  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You use the scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene/1519864-anchorpoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to orient the default screen position of its nodes. For example, setting the scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "anchorPoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " makes child nodes with a position of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " display at the bottom-left corner of the scene. However, setting the scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "anchorPoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0.5,0.5)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " makes child nodes with a position of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " display in the center of the scene. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You only use the scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "anchorPoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for scene's that don't have a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene/1519696-camera"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". If, however, you set a scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "camera"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", then the camera drives which portion of the scene is visible at any given time, and the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "anchorPoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is ignored. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Set the Scene's Origin to the Bottom-Left of its View",
          "anchor": "3020372"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, a scene’s origin is placed in the lower-left corner of the view, as shown in the figure below. A scene initialized with a height of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1024"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and a width of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "768"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " has the origin "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in the lower-left corner, and the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(1024,768)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " coordinate in the upper-right corner. The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483026-frame"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property holds "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0)-(1024,768)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A scene’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483101-position"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property is ignored by Scene Kit because the scene is always the root node for a node tree. Its default value is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgpoint/1454433-zero"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and you can’t change it. However, you can move the scene’s origin by setting its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene/1519864-anchorpoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. The anchor point is specified in the unit coordinate space and chooses a point in the enclosing view."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3020373",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3020373",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Default anchor for a scene is in the lower-left corner of the view"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default value for the anchor point is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgpoint/1454433-zero"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which places it at the lower-left corner. The scene’s visible coordinate space is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(width,height)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The default anchor point is most useful for games that do not scroll a scene’s content."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Center the Scene's Origin Within its View",
          "anchor": "3020375"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The second-most common anchor point value is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0.5,0.5)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which centers the scene’s origin in the middle of the view as shown in the figure below. The scene’s visible coordinate space is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(-width/2,-height/2)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(width/2,height/2)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Centering the scene on its anchor point is most useful when you want to easily position nodes relative to the center of the screen, such as in a scrolling game. However, this effect is better achieved using a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skcameranode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3020376",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3020376",
                "title": "Figure 2",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Moving the anchor point to the center of the view"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As a result of setting the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "anchorPoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "size"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", you indirectly set the scene’s frame, which determines the portion of the scene that's visible to the user."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
